Day 26 – 30 Days LeetCode SQL Challenge

 Problem: 586 – Customer Placing the Largest Number of Orders

✅ Problem Summary

You are given a table Orders:

order_number, 

customer_number

Each row represents one order placed by a customer.

👉 You need to find the customer who placed the most orders.

It is guaranteed that only one customer has the maximum orders.



🧠 SQL Solution



SELECT customer_number

FROM Orders

GROUP BY customer_number

ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC

LIMIT 1;



